Without specifying the `hexColor` method via [link:is/_], checking any input will always return `null`.

~~~ .php
// This will return `null` because `Is::hexColor()` method does not exist
if (Is::hexColor('#000')) {
    echo 'Is a HEX color.';
} else {
    echo 'Is not a HEX color.';
}
~~~

**Result:**

~~~ .txt
Is not a HEX color.
~~~
